There are moments in life that are too sacred and deep to put into words.  There are experiences that take eternity to unpack.  This was the case in our most recent visit to Canaan, The Evangelical Sisters of Mary.  They are an evangelical charismatic sisterhood, founded by Mother Basilea Schlink.  They have dedicated their lives to love the Lord Jesus with all they are.  17 years ago, I visited them as a hungry but ambitious young seeker.  The mixture in my heart was quickly revealed by their simplicity and the holy Presence of Jesus among them. Everything changed that day.  It has been 10 years since my last trip to their headquarters in Darmstadt, Germany.  Oh, what a blessed time we had with them this week.  It has been one of the deepest times I have had in Jesus in my entire life.  To love Him is to achieve something great.  To be there with Him when the world mocks Him is a holy privilege.  To endure what life throws at us with Him is a sacred invitation.  The sisters have become my dear friends over the years and I am so grateful for their love and support.  We worshipped, broke bread, shed tears, looked to the scriptures, prayed, laughed and spoke about our precious Bridegroom.  It felt like a piece of Heaven.  Tonight, we celebrate Great and Holy Friday.  We will meditate on the Lord’s passion and receive communion our church family in Orlando. Thank you, Jesus for your suffering and cross.  Amen.
What a gift it was to be with Brother Yun and @isaacliu316 at their church in Germany.  What a blessing this family is to us all.  They have paid a dear price for the Gospel 🕊🕊🕊
We are so proud and honored to know our dear friend @bendavidfitzgerald. Their church is thriving in Germany and what an honor it was to serve Jesus and this house. Lord, build Your house.

We’re so excited about this opportunity for Jesus School students! Students who have completed their first or second year of Jesus School are eligible for transferable credits with Regent University, Faith International University, and Logos University!

Regent University
Receive up to 9 transfer credits towards a degree at Regent University, and a 20% discount on the credit hour cost of tuition. Students must complete 2 years of Jesus School. 
 
Faith International University 
Receive up to 30 transfer credits towards a degree at FIU, a 33% discount on tuition, and an opportunity to earn additional credit at an accelerated rate. Students who complete the 1st year of Jesus School are eligible to receive 15 credits. Students who complete the 2nd year of Jesus School are eligible to receive 30 credits.
 
Logos University 
Receive up to 30 transfer credits towards a degree at Logos University. With a credit hour cost of $100, students are able to finish their degree at an affordable rate. Students who complete the 1st year of Jesus School are eligible to receive 15 credits. Students who complete the 2nd year of Jesus School are eligible to receive 30 credits. 

For more information or to apply for Fall 2023 at Jesus School and House of Bethany: Worship Academy, visit jesusschool.tv or the link in my bio!

Make Me a Bethany has been a prayer in my heart for years for @jesus_image and our community. During an intimate worship set at Jesus School one of our students began singing the line, “Make Me a Bethany”. Over the next couple of days, the verses came from the Lord and the rest of the chorus soon followed. The team felt a sense of ease and clarity as they came back together to finish the song. The first time it was sung during a Thursday Morning Worship set, there wasn’t a dry eye in the room. The song has become an anthem for us, it’s what we truly burn for. There is only one thing that’s needed — Jesus. As we sing these words of beautiful surrender, we long only to move His heart. Lord, make us a Bethany.
